Lovecopfry is described in Jeake’s Charters as a word connected with mercantile pursuits, but l cannot find any authority for such an interpretation. lt appears to bea term peculiar to the Cinque Ports, and may possibly mean free from toll on sale or purchase of commodities.

ln a manuscript note on the margin of the copy of Jealte’s work, now in the Bodleian Library, it is suggested that it means the right of having brothels in a town without the royal or episcopal licente.

Utviethis, from utviethum probably asa nominative, l have not discovered in any book of reference, and have therefore been compelled to give a translation of my own. l have sought to connect it with vieo, to bind with twigs, and have interpreted it as weit-baskets.
